The paper proposes a deep learning-based method for estimating multitype cardiac indices from MR images. The method involves joint learning of image representation and regression models using a convolutional autoencoder and a multiple output convolutional neural network. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the use of deep neural networks for regression, which falls under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also deals with medical imaging, which is a sub-field of multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks for estimation, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
